last_episode_to_air.name: Grace's Garden
last_episode_to_air.overview: Robert races to safety when a croc called Casper attacks during a feed; Tragedy strikes after urgent repairs begin on the Rainforest Aviary, and Bindi hand-raises a possum joey called Bonnie; Later, baby Grace receives a surprise honor.

name: Crikey! It's the Irwins
overview: Follow Terri, Bindi and Robert Irwin as they run the extraordinary Australia Zoo in the bushlands of northern Australia. Caring for over 1,200 animals, overseeing a world-class wildlife hospital, and conducting high-octane global conservation expeditions, the Irwins’ lives are full of adventure, fueled by their love of animals and passion for protecting them.

seasons.name: Season 3
seasons.overview: After a year of persevering through bushfire rescue efforts and a surreal global pandemic lockdown, the Irwins reopen the Australian Zoo and get back to the exciting business of caring for their beloved animals.

episodes.name: Steve’s Legacy Continues
episodes.overview: After months of croc wrangling training with Steve Irwin's best friend Wes, Robert, Steve's son, takes the final step in his journey to feed Graham, a huge crocodile at the zoo's famous Crocoseum.

episodes.name: Tiger Eyes
episodes.overview: Hunter the Sumatran tiger is blind and must be sedated for his annual eye check; the keepers prepare young giraffe Scarlett for a road trip to South Australia, reuniting her with family.

episodes.name: Giraffe Road Trip
episodes.overview: The family prepares Croc One, Steve Irwin's research ship, for a mission to release an endangered sea turtle back to the wild; Scarlett the giraffe reunites with her grandmother; Grub the wild echidna is released from the Zoo's Wildlife Hospital.

episodes.name: Robert, King of Cobras
episodes.overview: Robert wrangles Utah, a venomous 12-foot king cobra; Dr. Amber visits Tandora to care for wild koalas; back at the zoo, an old injury flares up for Bruce the brolga, a bird that has been in the Irwins' care for 26 years.

episodes.name: Bindi's Lemur Island
episodes.overview: The Australia Zoo's alligator snapping turtles need a health check, and it's Robert's job to protect from their fierce bites; Terri and Bindi welcome seven new lemurs from the United States; the Rescue Unit must save possums caught in a chimney.

episodes.name: Irwin African Adventure
episodes.overview: The Irwins travel to South Africa, where Terri helps release a wild leopard, Bindi learns from the all-female anti-poaching squad The Black Mambas and Robert attempts to photograph Africa's big five game animals.

episodes.name: It’s a Baby Giraffe!
episodes.overview: Rosie the giraffe is ready to give birth; Robert has a bloody encounter with a wild python that has entered an enclosure; Terri helps the keepers wrangle Chief the Tasmanian devil.

episodes.name: Robert's Baby Kangaroo
episodes.overview: Bindi and the keepers ready Sophie the Baby Giraffe for her first steps into her enclosure; Robert helps to hand-raise Melman the Kangaroo; Terri oversees a health check for Ravi the Red Panda.

episodes.name: Race to Save the Platypus
episodes.overview: Terri welcomes Mballa, a new cheetah cub from South Africa, to the Australia Zoo family; Robert sets out to save a stranded platypus and Bindi prepares to meet Bert the Koala Joey as he emerges from his mother's pouch for the first time.

episodes.name: Bindi & the Otters
episodes.overview: Wes and Robert remove eggs from the nest of saltwater crocodiles Terra and Bosco in a nerve-wracking but necessary venture; Bindi tends to the training of otters Percival and Daisy; Terri makes a zoo volunteer's dream come true.

episodes.name: Swimming With Manta Rays
episodes.overview: Robert travels to Australia's Great Barrier Reef to help conduct research on manta ray; the Zoo's Rescue Unit, Wildlife Hospital and Volunteers team up to save a baby wallaby struggling to survive.

episodes.name: Pawing Terri's Heart
episodes.overview: Terri attends the exam of Charlie the tiger to determine if his tumors were successfully treated; Bindi and the Small Mammal Team help develop a vaccine for Eden the Tasmanian devil; Robert discovers the true genders of the zoo's shingleback lizards.

episodes.name: Tortoise First Date
episodes.overview: Terri helps determine if Caballe the rhino is pregnant, while Robert hopes to get the zoo's Aldabra giant tortoises to mate

episodes.name: Steve's Croc Mission Lives On
episodes.overview: The family makes the annual trip to the Steve Irwin Wildlife Reserve to capture, study and release wild crocodiles, a mission started by Steve and Terri that provides research vital to the protection of Australia's apex predators.

episodes.name: Bosco the Croc's Big Move
episodes.overview: Robert takes on the challenging task of relocating Bosco, the most aggressive croc at the zoo. Bindi must investigate Forest the giraffe's bad knee problem. Terri helps Harley the koala find love at the end of a difficult breeding season.

episodes.name: Robert's Python Swim
episodes.overview: Robert gets in the water with Gloria, a 12-foot reticulated python, to swim alongside her for the first time in the Crocoseum. Bindi welcomes home two orphaned kangaroo joeys, while Terri helps release a rescued wedge-tailed eagle back into the wild.

episodes.name: Road Trip Rescue
episodes.overview: Carrying three baby kangaroos and an emu, the Irwins caravan into the Australian Outback to release the animals on Mourachan, their giant wildlife conservation property. Plans shift when they discover more animals in need of rescue along the way.

episodes.name: Big Day for Baby Rhino
episodes.overview: Terri helps prepare the zoo's new baby rhino to receive a lifesaving vaccine. Robert is on a rescue mission to save two black swans in very bad shape. Bindi tries to determine if a cranky wombat named Poa might be pregnant.

episodes.name: Crocodile Love Story
episodes.overview: It's moving day for Acco, the zoo's biggest crocodile. All goes to plan until his mate Cassie goes into hiding as the team races to reunite the bonded pair in their new enclosure. The rescue unit fights to save a flying fox entangled in barbed wire.

episodes.name: Oscar the Grouchy Frogmouth
episodes.overview: Terri returns to her hometown in Oregon to help Brady, a cougar in need of a vital health check. At the zoo, Robert is on a mission to rescue Oscar, a small bird with a big attitude, and Bindi bathes an echidna with bad skin allergies.

episodes.name: Swimming With Steve
episodes.overview: Bindi swims with Whale Sharks, assisting with research efforts on the worlds largest and least understood fish. Robert works to save an echidna that's tightly trapped under a fridge. Terri joins a close up exam on a Grizzly.

episodes.name: Robert Trains a Dragon
episodes.overview: Robert and Indah, a Komodo dragon, participate in an exciting research experiment. Terri tries to save a koala joey with a zero percent chance of survival. Bindi visits friends at childhood favorite spot Oregon Coast Aquarium.

episodes.name: Robert's Alligator Feeding Frenzy
episodes.overview: Robert feeds 44 hungry alligators, all at the same time. Terri helps examine Kaitlyn the tiger and makes a thrilling discovery, while Bindi follows the heartbreaking story of her old friend, Zambezi the zebra.

episodes.name: Turtles Take Flight
episodes.overview: Robert and Terri take to the skies to release three rescued sea turtles near the Great Barrier Reef. Bindi anxiously awaits the birth of the zoo's first tiger cub in years. Richie helps a baby wallaby in his struggle for survival.

episodes.name: Robert & The Rattlesnakes
episodes.overview: Robert wrangles Western Diamondback rattlesnakes in Arizona for the first time, learning techniques passed down by his dad. Terri helps save some of the hospital's tiniest patients: three baby feathertail gliders. Bindi chats with Occa the cockatoo.

episodes.name: Bindi Says Yes!
episodes.overview: As Bindi celebrates her 21st birthday, she gets a surprise proposal from her boyfriend, Chandler. Meanwhile, things get dangerous as Robert wrangles gators in thick mud. Terri helps with the momentous birth of a baby white rhino.

episodes.name: Bindi's Wedding
episodes.overview: Bindi and Chandler prepare for the happiest day of their lives. Weeks before their wedding day, the coronavirus pandemic causes them to make difficult and drastic changes to the wedding of their dreams, but in the end love prevails.

episodes.name: Australia Zoo Begins Again
episodes.overview: After weeks of being closed due to the global pandemic, the Irwins race to prepare for the re-opening of the zoo. Robert helps deliver a litter of newborn tiger cubs, while Bindi handles a sudden crisis at the wildlife hospital.

episodes.name: Tiger Triplets
episodes.overview: Bindi and the family plan an emotional surprise for Terri in the Crocoseum. Chandler must step up during the croc show, while Robert gets hands-on with the zoo’s newest members – three adorable tiger cubs.

episodes.name: Bushfire Rescue
episodes.overview: After historical wildfires rip through Australia, the Irwins race to rescue as many animals as possible. Robert and Terri jump in to help the severely injured koala population, while Bindi and the wildlife hospital rescue hundreds of baby flying foxes.

episodes.name: A Baby Giraffe's Tall Order
episodes.overview: After the birth of Talbert the giraffe, complications arise and the Irwins worry for his life. Robert rescues an entangled black swan caught in fishing line, while Bindi and Chandler plan for Kingston the rhino's first birthday.

episodes.name: Wildlife Hospital Warriors
episodes.overview: Terri and Bindi join the team at The Australia Zoo Wildlife Hospital as they treat an incredible range of animals, including a complex koala surgery which pushes both of them beyond their limits. Robert and Chandler join the rescue unit.

episodes.name: Double Puggle
episodes.overview: It’s an exciting time as Bindi and the zoo welcome two baby echidnas, but health concerns become a major threat for one puggle’s survival. Robert has fun preparing Douglas the jabiru for his first arrival in the Crocoseum, until he goes missing.

episodes.name: Robert And Big Bad Bosco
episodes.overview: Robert continues his father’s legacy as he faces off with Bosco, the most aggressive croc at the zoo. Bindi lends a hand when Claire the koala needs critical eye surgery, and Forest attempts to break the record for the World’s Tallest Giraffe.

episodes.name: Bindi's Croc Trip Surprise
episodes.overview: The Irwins return to the Steve Irwin Wildlife Reserve to study crocodiles. It’s an epic trip as Robert leads the croc catching team for the very first time, while Bindi and Chandler reveal a life-changing announcement.

episodes.name: Komodo Connection
episodes.overview: An anxious Robert looks on when Indah the Komodo Dragon meets Gili, an aggressive potential mating partner. Terri handles a mysterious lump inside Jessie the woma python, and Bindi and Chandler study coral bleaching on the Great Barrier Reef.

episodes.name: Backyard Croc Rescue
episodes.overview: It’s a monumental day for the zoo as they welcome four Sumatran elephants. Robert rescues a crocodile from a suburban backyard before he and Terri secretly try to guess the gender of Bindi’s baby, but Bindi and Chandler have their own surprise in store.

episodes.name: Nothing Stops Bindi
episodes.overview: Steve’s lifelong dream of breeding cassowaries, one of the most dangerous birds in the world, may become reality when 6 eggs are laid. A very pregnant Bindi continues to assist the Wildlife Hospital and Oberon the baby gator makes his Crocoseum debut.

episodes.name: Stormin' Norman
episodes.overview: The Irwins take action when Norman, the Zoo’s favorite croc, becomes critically ill. Robert prepares a trio of tiger cubs to unite with their older brother Nelson for the very first time, and Terri welcomes five fluffy koala joeys from Kangaroo Island.

3.name: Season 3
3.overview: After a year of persevering through bushfire rescue efforts and a surreal global pandemic lockdown, the Irwins reopen the Australian Zoo and get back to the exciting business of caring for their beloved animals.

episodes.name: Robert's Great Gator Challenge
episodes.overview: History is made at the Australia Zoo when Robert and team attempt the largest alligator capture and relocation; koala breeding takes a tough turn for Bindi and the Wildlife Hospital; Terri gives the Sumatran elephants more space to roam.

episodes.name: Bad Boy Bunker
episodes.overview: Robert handles an aggressive wombat called Bunker, and it's moving day for a giant anaconda called Nikki; Terri helps treat hundreds of lorikeets injured by a hailstorm; Later, Robert and Chandler team up to bake a special treat for the Irwin ladies.

episodes.name: Terri's Wonder Wallaby
episodes.overview: Terri responds to the call when Daniel, a very special wallaby, becomes severely injured and cannot walk; Robert and Chandler catch some waves before taking a road trip to pick up a new Komodo dragon; Bindi checks in on Tallbert the giraffe calf.

episodes.name: The Puggle Struggle
episodes.overview: Chandler must handle a koala crisis, while Terri lends a hand to care for an influx of puggles; A turtle called Billy undergoes a critical surgery, and Bindi recruits Chandler and Robert to bake a special wombat birthday surprise.

episodes.name: Tiny But Poisonous
episodes.overview: Bindi welcomes the arrival of tiny poison dart frogs to their new home at the zoo; Terri takes charge when the crew moves Bosco out of the Crocoseum; Chandler helps a glider called Kronk.

episodes.name: Grace's Garden
episodes.overview: Robert races to safety when a croc called Casper attacks during a feed; Tragedy strikes after urgent repairs begin on the Rainforest Aviary, and Bindi hand-raises a possum joey called Bonnie; Later, baby Grace receives a surprise honor.
